               <head>Ramz va isharaha-yi 'Alamgiri</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Ramz va ishārahā-yi ʿĀlamgīrī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n2013007835 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115921 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115922 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85076229 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85104368" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4004-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1897">Ramz va ishārahā-yi ʿĀlamgīrī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_1897">رمز و اشارهاى عالم گيرى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Anonymously compiled, collection of orders and private letters or shuqqah of the Timurid or Mughal ruler, Emperor ʿĀlamgīr (d. 1707)</p>
                        <p>At least 21 letters differ from or are not contained in IO Islamic 4003, and are thus of value</p>
                        <p>Collection concludes with a section on anecdotes and pronouncements relating to or by ʿĀlamgīr</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Transcribed by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">G. J. Nicholls</persName>, Judge at <name type="place">Farrukhabad</name>, from a manuscript obtained from <name type="place">Agra</name>Copied from an original manuscript belonging to the library of 
                     </note>
                     <filiation>Copied from a manuscript belonging to the library of Sayyid Amān Allāh Ḥusaynī at Benares (Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh), fawjdār of the city during ʿĀlamgīr's reign. Mediation provided by Mr Loyat / Levitt (?) Ṣāḥib Bahādur, collector of Benares.</filiation>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
